---

## ğŸš€ Quick Start

### 1. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 2. Prepare your dataset

Your `data.csv` must have at least these two columns:

| Column | Description                        |
|--------|------------------------------------|
| `Body` | Full article text                  |
| `Label`| Ground-truth label (`REAL`/`FAKE`) |

### 3. Train the model

```bash
python fake_news_detector.py
```

This will:
- Train and evaluate the classifier
- Print metrics to the console
- Save `confusion_matrix.png` and `metrics.png`
- Save the model to `model/`

### 4. Predict on new articles

```python
from fake_news_detector import load_model, predict

pac, vectorizer = load_model("model")

result = predict("Scientists discover new vaccine with 95% efficacy.", pac, vectorizer)
print(result)
# â†’ {'label': 'REAL', 'confidence': 0.87}
```

---

## ğŸ“Š Model Details

| Component       | Configuration                          |
|-----------------|----------------------------------------|
| Vectorizer      | TF-IDF, bigrams, max 50k features, sublinear TF |
| Classifier      | Passive Aggressive, C=0.5, early stopping |
| Train/Test Split| 80% / 20%, stratified                 |

